From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
Subject: [ldn_mitm] Integrate switch-lan-play relay bridge via IPC channel

Wire ldn_mitm into the switch-lan-play relay so that "wireless local" games
work over the internet.  Communication with the relay server is entirely UDP.

Key changes
-----------
1. lanplay_bridge.{hpp,cpp}
   Reads sdmc:/tmp/lanplay.status (written by switch-lan-play every 2 s).
   Exposes:  lanplay_is_active(), lanplay_get_virtual_ip(),
             lanplay_get_broadcast(), lanplay_get_ipc_sockaddr()
   Cache: ~1 second (19 200 000 Switch CPU ticks = 19.2 MHz clock).

2. LDUdpSocket::sendBroadcast overrides  (lan_discovery.cpp / .hpp)
   When switch-lan-play is active, each outbound LAN-discovery broadcast
   (e.g. Scan) is ALSO sent to 127.0.0.1:LDN_IPC_PORT (11453).  The
   sysmodule's IPC thread receives it, wraps it as a synthetic IPv4+UDP
   frame, and forwards it to the relay server over UDP.
   This is cleaner than SO_REUSEPORT because:
     - No loop-prevention logic needed (loopback is always local traffic).
     - Does not require port sharing with ldn_mitm's main UDP socket.

3. getFakeMac() / getNodeInfo()  use the virtual IP (10.13.x.y) instead of
   the real WiFi IP so that station-to-AP TCP connections use the relay path.

4. getBroadcast() returns 10.13.255.255 so Scan packets travel through the
   relay rather than the real WiFi broadcast domain.

5. initialize() skips nifmSetLocalNetworkMode(true) when switch-lan-play is
   active; that call disables internet access and would sever the relay UDP
   connection.

Apply with: patch -p1 -d ldn_mitm < patches/0001-lanplay-bridge.patch

